    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Trenton, N. J.</placeName>
                <date>March 14th 1864</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <add>יום ב ו' אדר שני תרכ"ד לפ"ק</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><add>שלום וכל טוב סלה Rev. I. Leeser in</add>
                <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee> in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><persName role="author">A. I. Rosenthal</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">care of <persName>Mr. Julius Schloss</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <placeName>Trenton, N. J.</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Trenton N. J.</placeName>
                <date>March 14, 1864</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The second day of the week, the inst day<lb/> of the month
                    <date>Odor the second 5624</date> according<lb/> our chronology.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Peace &amp; happiness Amen.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee> in
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Your valuable <add>?</add> from <date>29th of Odor<lb/> the first</date>, reached me
                in time, and I am<lb/> taking the liberty to answer you with the highest
                respect<lb/> that I didn't look for other <add>?</add> yet.<lb/> I wouldn't spill
                dirty water, till I'll<lb/> get clean one. It is an old proverb<lb/> (saying) but it
                is true.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">II</p>
            <p>In reference to the position<add>?</add>, that<lb/> you are writing me, I know how
                to<lb/> appreciate and I am very much obliged<lb/> and thankful for your kind
                intention<lb/> I would like to call your attention<lb/> that I wouldn't accept any
                position<lb/> unless I'll be sure, that the community<lb/> that offers the position
                has a congregation<lb/> where I'll be able without any<lb/> difficulties to have a
                    <add>Hebrew</add> (is<lb/> mean <add>?</add> ten Jews the minimum number<lb/>
                needed to start services.) each <date>Friday</date> evening.</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">III</p>
            <p>and <date>Saturday</date> morning and minchats<add>?</add><lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add> except this I would <del>like</del><lb/> prefer to make a nice
                living that<lb/> I shall be able as a human<lb/>
                <sic>beign</sic>, and a Jew to enjoy my life, and as<lb/> far it is not a suitable
                community.<lb/> I have no desire to suffer unjustly<lb/> on such a far distant
                place. These are<lb/> my aspect which I share with you<lb/> I hope that with the
                help of god I'll<lb/> have the opportunity to talk to you<lb/> personally.</p>
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <sic>II</sic>
            </p>
            <p>&amp; with respect and devotion<lb/>
                <add>?</add> inquiring.<lb/> The young man <persName role="author">Abraham
                    Isaacs</persName><lb/> the son of the respectful</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName>David Rosenthal</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
